1.definition: Alteration that selectively replaces specific bands within rocks.

2.definition: Alteration that selectively replaces specific beds within sedimentary rocks.

3.definition: Alteration associated with a fissure containing cemented wallrock fragments.

4.definition: Alteration associated with a fault displaying angular rock fragments resulting from fracturing.

5.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a fault.

6.definition: Alteration confined to volumes of rocks exhibiting a foliation.

7.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a fracture, i.e. with any break/separation in a geological formation with or without relative displacement of the parts (e.g. a joint or a fault).

8.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a breccia.

9.definition: Alteration restricted to compositionally or texturally defined layers within rocks.

10.definition: Alteration that has replaced or filled in only certain portions of the rock at the scale of observation (e.g. the envelopes around veins), certain primary minerals, or pore spaces (including vesicles and interclast voids).

11.definition:
Alteration characterized by the replacement of most, or all, original rock-forming minerals and obliteration of textures at the scale of observation.

Lots more info here...

12.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of only specific components (e.g. minerals, grains, clasts) of the original rock, with partial to complete obliteration of textures at the scale of observation.

13.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of only specific components (e.g. minerals, grains, clasts) of the original rock, with partial to complete obliteration of textures only in part of the area under observation.

14.definition: Alteration characterized by the replacement of only specific components (e.g. minerals, grains, clasts) of the original rock, with partial to complete obliteration of textures across the whole area of observation.

15.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a shear zone.

16.definition: Alteration spatially restricted to rocks within and/or immediately adjacent to structures such as shear zones, fault zones, veins, hydrothermal breccias, vugs or fractures.

17.definition: A rock with no visible signs of alteration, in which primary minerals, fabrics (including primary pore space) and chemistry are unchanged.XXX

18.definition: Alteration that occurs at or around an unconformable or disconformable contact.

19.definition: Alteration spatially associated with a vein.

20.definition: Alteration associated with small cavities in a vein or rock, usually lined with crystals of a different mineral composition from the enclosing rock.

21.definition: Alteration that can be divided spatially into several mineralogically or texturally distinct regions, with systematic variations in mineral assemblages, compositions and/or textures.

22.definition: The central region of an alteration zone

23.definition: The inner region of an alteration zone.

24.definition: The outer region of an alteration zone.

25.definition: An enclave within New South Wales containing the national capital, Canberra.

26.definition: The most populous state, located on the east coast. Capital: Sydney. XXX

27.definition: A territory in the centre and central north of the continent. Capital: Darwin.

28.definition: The second-largest state, occupying the northeast. Capital: Brisbane.

29.definition: A southern state bordered by all other mainland states and the Northern Territory. Capital: Adelaide.

30.definition: The six federated states of Australia.

31.definition: An island state south of the mainland. Capital: Hobart.

32.definition: The major self-governing internal territories of Australia.

33.definition: A southeastern state and the smallest on the mainland. Capital: Melbourne.

34.definition: The largest state by area, covering the western third of the continent. Capital: Perth.

35.definition: A tertiary colour between yellow and orange.

36.definition: A cool primary colour between green and violet in the visible spectrum.

37.definition: A tertiary colour between yellow and green.

38.definition: A secondary colour made by mixing blue and yellow.

39.definition: A tertiary colour between blue and purple.

40.definition: A tertiary colour between red and purple.

41.definition: A secondary colour made by mixing red and yellow.

42.definition: A colour that cannot be made by mixing other colours.

43.definition: A secondary colour made by mixing red and blue.

44.definition: A warm primary colour at the long-wavelength end of the visible spectrum.

45.definition: A colour made by mixing two primary colours.

46.definition: A tertiary colour between blue and green.

47.definition: A colour made by mixing a primary colour with a neighbouring secondary colour.

48.definition: A tertiary colour between red and orange.

49.definition: A warm primary colour between green and orange in the visible spectrum.

50.definition: Project is approved and work is in progress.

51.definition: Project is paused due to an external dependency or unresolved issue.

52.definition: Project has been permanently stopped before completion.

53.definition: All project deliverables have been finished and accepted.

54.definition: Project has been proposed but not yet approved or started.

55.definition: Tasks are currently being worked on.

56.definition: Deliverables are under review by stakeholders.

57.definition: Project is temporarily paused pending resolution of blockers.

58.definition: Project is paused while waiting for approval to proceed.
